The Odyssey - In Theaters 07.17.26

Christopher Nolan‚Äôs next film, The Odyssey, is a mythic action epic shot across the world using brand new IMAX¬Æ film technology. The film brings Homer‚Äôs foundational saga to IMAX¬Æ film screens for the first time and opens in theaters everywhere on July 17, 2026. 

The Odyssey stars Matt Damon, Tom Holland, Anne Hathaway, Robert Pattinson and Lupita Nyong‚Äôo, with Zendaya and Charlize Theron.

The Odyssey is produced by Emma Thomas and Christopher Nolan for their company, Syncopy. The executive producer is Thomas Hayslip.

They are not just pets, but the melody of our family ‚Äî the laughter in our days, the harmony in our hearts, and the purest chorus of unconditional love. In their presence, life feels brighter, softer, and endlessly more beautiful. This song is for them, our eternal companions, our family‚Äôs sweetest joy.

snippet.description:
Sri Godadevi Chalisa Telugu | Sri Lakshmi Devi Chalisa | Dhanurmasam Special | Goddess Andal Songs | Goddess Lakshmi Devi Songs 

Sri Godadevi Chalisa Telugu and Godadevi Songs Telugu glorify the divine devotion of Andal Devi through soulful Andal Devi Chalisa and Sri Andal Devotional Songs Telugu. During the sacred Dhanurmasam Special Songs, devotees immerse themselves in Godadevi Bhakti Songs and traditional Andal Dhanurmasam Songs, offering heartfelt prayers. The serene flow of Vishnu Bhakti Telugu Songs blends beautifully with Dhanurmasam Pooja Songs, creating a sacred atmosphere. Through Sri Godadevi Bhakthi Geethalu, devotees celebrate pure devotion and divine grace during the auspicious Dhanurmasam.

Listen to the divine Sri Godadevi Chalisa, dedicated to Goddess Godadevi (Andal), the eternal consort of Lord Vishnu. This special devotional song is offered during the sacred month of Dhanurmasam, an auspicious time for bhakti, vratham, and Vishnu worship.

Listen to the best collection of Sri Lakshmi Devi and Sri Godadevi Bhakthi Songs, dedicated to the divine goddesses of wealth, prosperity, devotion, and spiritual blessings.

These powerful devotional songs help bring peace, positivity, abundance, and divine grace into your life. Ideal for daily prayers, Margasiramasam worship, festivals, and meditation.

üôè Chant and listen daily to receive the blessings of Goddess Lakshmi Devi and Sri Godadevi Ammavaru.

Welcome to our Tamil Devotional Channel, your ultimate destination for soulful and uplifting Tamil devotional songs. Dive into the divine with our carefully curated collections designed to inspire and bring peace to your soul every day of the week.

Daily Devotional Songs:

* Shiva Tamil Devotional Songs: Celebrate the power and grace of Lord Shiva.
* Vishnu Tamil Devotional Songs: Immerse in the blessings of Lord Vishnu.
* Muruga Tamil Devotional Songs: Invoke the valor and blessings of Lord Muruga.
* Hanuman Tamil Devotional Songs: Feel the strength and devotion of Lord Hanuman.
* Amman Tamil Devotional Songs: Honor the divine mother in her various forms.
* Saibaba Tamil Devotional Songs: Seek the blessings of Shirdi Sai Baba.
* Balaji Tamil Devotional Songs: Worship Lord Venkateswara with these soulful songs.
* Lakshmi Tamil Devotional Songs: Attract prosperity with hymns for Goddess Lakshmi.
* Devi Tamil Devotional Songs: Praise the supreme goddess Devi in her many avatars.
* Ganesh Tamil Devotional Songs: Start your day with prayers to Lord Ganesha.

Special Occasions and Deities:
* Amavasai Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs for the new moon day rituals.
* Pradosham Tamil Devotional Songs: Hymns for the auspicious Pradosham period.
* Ashta Lakshmi Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs dedicated to the eight forms of Goddess Lakshmi.
* Vinayagar Tamil Devotional Songs: Devotions for the remover of obstacles, Lord Vinayagar.
* Ganapathi Tamil Devotional Songs: Invoke blessings from Lord Ganapathi.
* Surya Tamil Devotional Songs: Worship the Sun God, Surya, with these melodies.
* Sani Tamil Devotional Songs: Appease Lord Sani with these devotional tracks.
* Guru Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs to honor Guru and seek his wisdom.
* Perumal Tamil Devotional Songs: Devote to Lord Perumal with these spiritual songs.
* Navagraha Tamil Devotional Songs: Balance your energies with songs for the nine planets.

Subscribe now and join our spiritual journey. Like, share, and hit the bell icon to stay updated with our latest devotional uploads. May these divine songs bring peace, prosperity, and positivity to your life.

Welcome to our Tamil Devotional Channel, your ultimate destination for soulful and uplifting Tamil devotional songs. Dive into the divine with our carefully curated collections designed to inspire and bring peace to your soul every day of the week.

Daily Devotional Songs:

* Muruga Tamil Devotional Songs: Invoke the valor and blessings of Lord Muruga.
* Hanuman Tamil Devotional Songs: Feel the strength and devotion of Lord Hanuman.
* Amman Tamil Devotional Songs: Honor the divine mother in her various forms.
* Saibaba Tamil Devotional Songs: Seek the blessings of Shirdi Sai Baba.

* Lakshmi Tamil Devotional Songs: Attract prosperity with hymns for Goddess Lakshmi.
* Devi Tamil Devotional Songs: Praise the supreme goddess Devi in her many avatars.
* Ganesh Tamil Devotional Songs: Start your day with prayers to Lord Ganesha.

Special Occasions and Deities:
* Amavasai Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs for the new moon day rituals.
* Pradosham Tamil Devotional Songs: Hymns for the auspicious Pradosham period.
* Ashta Lakshmi Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs dedicated to the eight forms of Goddess Lakshmi.
* Vinayagar Tamil Devotional Songs: Devotions for the remover of obstacles, Lord Vinayagar.
* Ganapathi Tamil Devotional Songs: Invoke blessings from Lord Ganapathi.
* Surya Tamil Devotional Songs: Worship the Sun God, Surya, with these melodies.
* Sani Tamil Devotional Songs: Appease Lord Sani with these devotional tracks.
* Guru Tamil Devotional Songs: Songs to honor Guru and seek his wisdom.
* Perumal Tamil Devotional Songs: Devote to Lord Perumal with these spiritual songs.
* Navagraha Tamil Devotional Songs: Balance your energies with songs for the nine planets.

snippet.title: Shinchan and Franklin  Celebrate Christmas with Santa Claus in GTA 5
snippet.description:
In this video Shinchan and Franklin  Celebrate Christmas with Santa Claus in GTA 5

In this fun and festive GTA 5 story mod, Franklin transforms his house into a Christmas wonderland, decorating it with sparkling lights and a massive Christmas tree. üåü

Franklin wants to spread joy to all his gang members, so he goes on a gift-hunting adventure! First, he surprises Shinchan with an amazing 3-wheeled blue bike, then grabs a super muscle car equipped with an RPG rocket launcher! üöóüí• But the holiday fun doesn‚Äôt stop there ‚Äî Franklin also buys delicious cake and wine for everyone in the gang. üéÇüç∑

Things get magical when Franklin meets Santa Claus on his rooftop! üéÖ Santa tells him about his second sleigh, parked near the Los Santos Dam Observatory. Franklin sets off on a mission to find this beautiful sleigh and bring it home.

Finally, it‚Äôs time for the big celebration! Franklin wakes up the gang, hands out all the gifts, and invites Chop and Shinchan for a thrilling ride on the sleigh. Together, they soar across the Los Santos skyline, enjoying the festive spirit and the joy of friendship. ‚ú®

Don‚Äôt miss this epic Christmas story full of laughter, surprises, and GTA 5 chaos!

snippet.description:
#Veeramanidaasan #AmmanSongs #melmaruvathuradhiparasakthi
#AmmanSongs #Tamildevotional #Veeramanidaasan #LREswari
 #melmaruvathuradhiparasakthi #melmaruvathur 

The album ‚ÄúOm Sakthiyea - ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø‡ÆØ‡Øá‚Äù is dedicated to Goddess Amman.
Sung By : L.R Eswari, Veeramani Dasan
Lyrics By : Mugilan
Music By : Kanmani Raja & D V Ramani
Produced By : Unique Recording

 Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You! Om Sakthi !

Do Like, Share, Comment & Subscribe to Bakthi Mahimai !

Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You! Om Sakthi !
